-- Truck Production in Germany May Increase 11% Next Year, VDA Group Predicts
-- B y   A n g e l a   C u l l e n
-- 2010-12-30T07:38:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/german-truck-production-may-climb-11-in-2011-vda-industry-group-says.html
Truck production in Germany may
increase 11 percent next year as demand fuels a recovery,
according to the VDA industry group.  “Although we haven’t returned to pre-crisis levels, the
upward trend is clearly visible,” VDA President Matthias
Wissmann said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  